# grapher_ineq_halfplane_smoke.numos — Phase 10D. Plot the linear inequality
# 2x+3>4+4y. lhs="2x+3" rhs="4+4y" (implicit multiplication 2x, 4y), G=2x-1-4y,
# solution G>0 i.e. y<(2x-1)/4 — a shaded half-plane below the boundary line.
# Proves multi-term linear inequalities with y on the right shade correctly.
# Warning-only (no golden); NOT CI-gated.
log "ineq halfplane: start"
wait 200
open_app Grapher
wait 60
key down
key enter
# Type "2x+3>4+4y"
key 2
key x
key +
key 3
key gt
key 4
key +
key 4
key y
key enter
wait 80
key graph
wait 120
screenshot out/grapher_ineq_halfplane_smoke.ppm
assert_app Grapher
log "ineq halfplane: 2x+3>4+4y shaded"
